All the songs in this film were composed by [[Bappi Lahiri]], and the lyrics were written by [[Indeewar]] and [[Anjaan (lyricist)|Anjaan]].<ref>{{cite web| title = Original Motion Pictures: Armaan (1981)| publisher = [[Saregama]]| url =http://www.saregama.com/portal/pages/film?mode=get_album_info&albumId=187454}}</ref> The [[Music of Bollywood|Bollywood]] [[disco]] song "Ramba Ho Ho Ho Samba Ho Ho Ho" was listed at #21 on [[Binaca Geetmala annual list 1981]]. Another popular song was "Mere Jaesi Haseena", a song in the [[Indo-Trinidadian|Indian-Trinidadian]] hybrid style known as [[Chutney music|Chutney]].<ref>{{cite news |title=12 x 12: The 12 best Bollywood disco records |url=https://thevinylfactory.com/features/12-x-12-the-12-best-bollywood-disco-records/ |work=[[The Vinyl Factory]] |date=28 February 2014}}</ref>

